PER CURIAM:Â  Stephen Henry Trotman appeals his convictions for armed robbery, carjacking, kidnapping, assault of a high and aggravated nature, and possession of a weapon during the commission of a crime of violence.Â  He argues the trial judge erred in denying his motion for a continuance.Â  Counsel for Trotman attached to the final brief a petition to be relieved as counsel, stating she had reviewed the record and concluded this appeal lacks merit.Â  Trotman filed a separate pro se brief.Â  After a thorough review of the record, counselâ€™s brief, and Trotmanâ€™s pro se brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738 (1967) and State v. Williams, 305 S.C. 116, 406 S.E.2d 357 (1991), we dismiss[1] the appeal and grant counselâ€™s petition to be relieved.
APPEAL DISMISSED.
HEARN, C.J., and BEATTY and SHORT, JJ., concur.

