PER CURIAM:Â  Terrance P. Cannon appeals his convictions for possession with intent to distributed (PWID) marijuana, PWID cocaine, and trafficking crack cocaine arguing the trial judge erred in trying him in absentia.Â  Counsel for Cannon attached to the final brief a petition to be relieved as counsel, stating she had reviewed the record and concluded this appeal lacks merit.Â  After a thorough review of the record and counselâ€™s brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738 (1967) and State v. Williams, 305 S.C. 116, 406 S.E.2d 357 (1991), we dismiss[1] the appeal and grant counselâ€™s petition to be relieved.
